#: ../../K/k-.rst:5
msgid "k-"
msgstr "k-"

#: ../../K/k-.rst:7
msgid "pref\\."
msgstr "接頭辞"

#: ../../K/k-.rst:9
msgid ""
"[rare; poss fr. kilo- prefix] Extremely. Rare among hackers, but quite "
"common among crackers and :ref:`warez-d00dz` in compounds such as k-kool "
"/K´kool´/, k-rad /K´rad´/, and k-awesome /K´aw\\`sm/. Also used to intensify"
" negatives; thus, k-evil, k-lame, k-screwed, and k-annoying. Overuse of this"
" prefix, or use in more formal or technical contexts, is considered an "
"indicator of :ref:`lamer` status."
msgstr ""
"[まれ。おそらくkilo-接頭辞より]極めて。ハッカーの間ではまれだが、クラッカーや\\ :ref:`warez-d00dz`\\ "
"の間では、k-kool /K´kool´/、k-rad /K´rad´/、k-awesome /K´aw\\`sm/ "
"のような複合語としてかなり一般的。否定を強めるのにも使われる。すなわち、k-evil、k-lame、k-screwed、k-annoying。この接頭辞を多用したり、より形式的・技術的な文脈で使ったりすることは、\\"
" :ref:`lamer`\\ の地位を示す指標とみなされる。"
